                <h1>Religious Significance of Easter Lilies</h1>
                <p>Your Easter lily, a symbol of purity and resurrection, holds deep religious significance, especially during the Easter season. Associated with the Virgin Mary's purity, these elegant flowers bloom in spring, representing new life and renewal. Used in churches and home decorations, they enhance the sacred ambiance of Easter celebrations.</p>
